videos.description: Chris Boucher tries to personally destroy the basketball with a vicious block, but Georgetown is able to collect the loose ball and score the basket.
videos.headline: Boucher with a vicious rejection, but Georgetown scores

videos.description: 1H (5:22) ORE Payton Pritchard made Layup. Assisted by Casey Benson.
videos.headline: Oregon with some good passing on the fast break leads to the reverse layup

videos.description: Georgetown has jumped out on Oregon in Maui, especially after L.J. Peak hits the 3-pointer from the top of the arc and gets the foul to put the Hoyas lead into double digits.
videos.headline: Peak drains the 3-pointer and-1 for Georgetown
Oregon uses great hustle to keep the ball alive and get the basket

videos.description: With the first half clock winding down, Rodney Pryor lets it go on the run to drain the 3-pointer, putting Georgetown up 17 points on Oregon in Maui.
videos.headline: Pryor drills wild shot to beat halftime buzzer for Georgetown
Rodney Pryor uses two crossovers and hits the jumper

videos.description: After trailing by as many as 18, Oregon is roaring back thanks to Dylan Ennis getting the offensive rebound and dishing it off to Jordan Bell for the huge slam over a defender.
videos.headline: Bell's monster slam has Oregon storming back
Back to Back blocks for Oregon

videos.description: 2H (0:07) ORE Dillon Brooks made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Payton Pritchard.
videos.headline: Deep 3 pointer for Dillon Brooks
